<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1968] Thrift&apos;s include path is wrong in pkg-config files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1968</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It seems like thrift&apos;s pkg-config files are pointing to a wrong include path.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve installed thrift 0.9.0 (and rechecked with git&apos;s master) like this:&lt;br/&gt;
  ./configure --prefix=/opt/thrift&lt;br/&gt;
  make&lt;br/&gt;
  sudo make install&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now I have, e.g. this file:&lt;br/&gt;
  /opt/thrift/include/thrift/Thrift.h&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, at this point I&apos;m not able to include &amp;lt;thrift/Thrift.h&amp;gt;, because&lt;br/&gt;
  pkg-config thrift --cflags&lt;br/&gt;
returns:&lt;br/&gt;
  -I/opt/thrift/include/thrift&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which means I should include &amp;lt;Thrift.h&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Page &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.apache.org/thrift/ThriftUsageC%2B%2B&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.apache.org/thrift/ThriftUsageC%2B%2B&lt;/a&gt; suggests including files without the &quot;thrift/&quot; prefix. But the generated code does contain the prefix...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Am I doing something wrong, or is it actually a bug and thrift should install headers with one more directory in the path, e.g:&lt;br/&gt;
  ${PREFIX}/include/thrift-0.9.0/thrift&lt;br/&gt;
That&apos;s the way some other libraries are doing it, e.g. gtk+.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Gentoo Linux&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
